escription: For students who have not registered. Payment Deadline: Payment is due by 6:00 p.m. the same day that you register. If you fail to pay fees, your classes may be canceled and you will have to re-register for available courses. Advising All new and undergraduate students must attend orientation before they can register. For information, see orientation.unt.edu or contact the Office of New Student Programs at 940-565-4198. Late Registration Schedule for All Students(for students that have no classes scheduled) Select Student Center/Register after logging in at my.unt.edu. Date Details January 13-18 Registration is available online at my.unt.edu from 7:00 a.m., January 13 - 5:30 p.m., January 18 Note: Registration will be unavailable from 5:30 p.m. to 11:59 p.m., January 18. Fee Payment Payment is due the same day that you register. If you fail to pay fees, your classes may be canceled and you will have to re-register for available courses. Bills will not be mailed for the Spring semester. Go to the Student Center online at my.unt.edu for your account balance and schedule information. Account balance information will be available at my.unt.edu once you complete registration. Go to the myUNT Student Center to view your bill. For more information about making payments, please visit studentaccounting.unt.edu. For information about Financial Aid and Scholarships, visit financialaid.unt.edu. Additional Resources For more information, contact the Registrar's Information Counter by calling 940-565-2378 or visiting Eagle Student Services Center (ESSC) Room 147. For instructions on using the myUNT Student Center for Registration, please visit Student Center Help.   Registration Info Find Classes Get Advised   Registration GuidesSpring 2017 Summer 2017 Fall 2017 Academic Catalog View All Forms Instructions for using MyUNT and EIS   Contact Information: Office of the Registrar 1155 Union Circle #311400 Denton, TX 76203-1400 USA Voice: 940-565-2111 Visit Us: Eagle Stude